article.headline: Lehigh 61, Colgate 56
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Austen Rowland was 5-for-8 from 3-point range and scored 25 points to lead Lehigh to a 61-56 victory over Colgate on Sunday. Rowland scored 10 points in the first 5 minutes as Lehigh (13-7, 6-1 Patriot League) took a 12-2 lead. Colgate (10-10, 2-5) used an 8-0 run to get back in the game and trailed 28-26 at halftime. Rowland's two 3-pointers and a layup early in the second half gave Lehigh a 46-35 lead. Colgate took a 53-52 lead with 1:42 remaining on a short jumper by Andrew Zidar. But Rowland hit a 3 from the top of the key to make it 55-53 and put Lehigh up for good. The Mountain Hawks were 9-for-9 from the free throw line. Jason Mgebroff had 13 points and eight rebounds for Lehigh, while Nick Monserez had a season-high 10 rebounds. Zidar led Colgate with 18 points, and Kendall Chones had 10 points and 11 rebounds.
